<TITLE> Hasina unwell, cancels engagements </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)Awami League president Sheikh Hasina was forced to cancel her engagements Sunday morning, on account of illness, aides have said. The former prime minister is suffering from hypertension, fever and fits of vomiting, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad and personal assistant Dr Awlad Hossain told bdnews24.com. A feverish Hasina cancelled her morning engagements, including visits to the Martyred Intellectuals' Graveyard, Rayerbazar Killing Grounds and Bangabandhu portrait, they said. "Hasina was feeling faint and stumbled while she was climbing downstairs this morning," Azad told bdnews24.com. Dr Awlad said the leader might attend a meeting scheduled for the afternoon if her condition improves. "Hasina has asked her countrymen to pray for her speedy recovery," he said. Hasina was also unable to attend the opening of her party's media centre Saturday afternoon, with presidium member Motia Chowdhury stepping in for her instead. The AL president could not inaugurate the media centre on account of illness, Motia had said. "Sheikh Hasina has been suffering from fever since (Saturday) morning." bdnews2
